OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FDry and bright but chilly
OL,6,Fstart, becoming cloudy later this
OL,7,Fmorning with outbreaks of rain and
OL,8,Fhill snow from late morning the snow
OL,9,Fmainly over northwest Perthshire. The
OL,10,Fwind will strengthen towards the
OL,11,Fevening.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FCloudy with further rain,
OL,14,Fhill snow in north, gales or severe
OL,15,Fgales for a time. Becoming drier and
OL,16,Fclearer overnight with winds easing.
OL,17,
OL,18,CSunday:FA dry and sunny morning.
OL,19,FCloudier for a time in afternoon with
OL,20,Fsome showers, wintry on high ground,
OL,21,Fbrighter again later.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
